						<summary>

						<p>Stone lying near the Āñjanēya temple outside the village.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Pushya śu. 12.</p>						

						<p>Wornout. Seems to record a gift of land to the learned Brāhmaṇas of the village. In characters of about the 16th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
